# create_prototype (project)

When the user wants an **Intuit Security Center** style HTML prototype—including `/create_prototype`, “create prototype”, “build the mockup”, or similar:

1. **Read** `.cursor/skills/create_prototype/SKILL.md` from this repo and follow it for layout, tokens, components, and the Figma spec section.
2. If they did not provide a **feature name** (kebab-case file) and **PRD / requirements** inline, **ask** for both before generating files.
3. Write a single self-contained **`<feature-name>-prototype.html`** at the **repository root** (no external assets).

This backs up the Agent Skill in `.cursor/skills/` if Skills are not attached or not discovered.
